Creating a simple game where the player controls the Godot logo can be done using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Below is a complete example of a web app that allows the player to move the Godot logo around the screen using the arrow keys.

You can copy and paste the following code into a single HTML file and open it in a web browser to play the game.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Godot Logo Game</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            overflow: hidden;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }
        #gameCanvas {
            position: relative;
            border: 2px solid #333;
            background-color: #fff;
        }
        #godotLogo {
            position: absolute;
            width: 100px; /* Adjust size as needed */
            height: auto;
            transition: transform 0.1s;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="gameCanvas" style="width: 800px; height: 600px;">
        <img id="godotLogo" src="https://godotengine.org/favicon.ico" alt="Godot Logo">
    </div>

    <script>
        const logo = document.getElementById('godotLogo');
        const canvas = document.getElementById('gameCanvas');
        const canvasRect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();

        let posX = canvasRect.width / 2 - 50; // Center the logo
        let posY = canvasRect.height / 2 - 50; // Center the logo

        logo.style.transform = `translate(${posX}px, ${posY}px)`;

        document.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {
            const step = 10; // Movement speed
            switch (event.key) {
                case 'ArrowUp':
                    posY = Math.max(0, posY - step);
                    break;
                case 'ArrowDown':
                    posY = Math.min(canvasRect.height - 100, posY + step); // 100 is the height of the logo
                    break;
                case 'ArrowLeft':
                    posX = Math.max(0, posX - step);
                    break;
                case 'ArrowRight':
                    posX = Math.min(canvasRect.width - 100, posX + step); // 100 is the width of the logo
                    break;
            }
            logo.style.transform = `translate(${posX}px, ${posY}px)`;
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Instructions:
1. Copy the code above.
2. Paste it into a new file and save it with a `.html` extension (e.g., `godot_game.html`).
3. Open the file in a web browser.

### How to Play:
- Use the arrow keys on your keyboard to move the Godot logo around the canvas.
- The logo will be constrained within the boundaries of the canvas.

Feel free to modify the logo size, movement speed, or canvas dimensions as needed!
